71text‚Äπ\linelabel{AOT_desc_spec}‚Ä∫
72specification(AOT_desc)
73  ‚Äï ‚ÄπDescriptions denote, if there is a unique denoting object satisfying the
74      matrix in the actual world.‚Ä∫
75  AOT_sem_desc_denotes: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ‚ùôŒπx(œÜ{x})‚Üì] = (‚àÉ! Œ∫ . [w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}])‚Ä∫
76  ‚Äï ‚ÄπDenoting descriptions satisfy their matrix in the actual world.‚Ä∫
77  AOT_sem_desc_prop: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ‚ùôŒπx(œÜ{x})‚Üì] ‚üπ [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{‚ùôŒπx(œÜ{x})}]‚Ä∫
78  ‚Äï ‚ÄπUniqueness of denoting descriptions.‚Ä∫
79  AOT_sem_desc_unique: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ‚ùôŒπx(œÜ{x})‚Üì] ‚üπ [w ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚üπ [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}] ‚üπ
80                        [w ‚ä® ‚ùôŒπx(œÜ{x}) = Œ∫]‚Ä∫
81proof -
82  have ‚Äπ‚àÉx::'a . ¬¨AOT_model_denotes x‚Ä∫
83    using AOT_model_nondenoting_ex
84    by blast
85  text‚ÄπNote that we may choose a distinct non-denoting object for each matrix.
86       We do this explicitly merely to convince ourselves that our specification
87       can still be satisfied.‚Ä∫
88  then obtain nondenoting :: ‚Äπ('a ‚áí ùóà) ‚áí 'a‚Ä∫ where
89    nondenoting: ‚Äπ‚àÄ œÜ . ¬¨AOT_model_denotes (nondenoting œÜ)‚Ä∫
90    by fast
91  define desc where
92    ‚Äπdesc = (Œª œÜ . if (‚àÉ! Œ∫ . [w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}])
93                   then (THE Œ∫ . [w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}])
94                   else nondenoting œÜ)‚Ä∫
95  {
96    fix œÜ :: ‚Äπ'a ‚áí ùóà‚Ä∫
97    assume ex1: ‚Äπ‚àÉ! Œ∫ . [w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}]‚Ä∫
98    then obtain Œ∫ where x_prop: "[w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}]"
99      unfolding AOT_sem_denotes by blast
100    moreover have "(desc œÜ) = Œ∫"
101      unfolding desc_def using x_prop ex1 by fastforce
102    ultimately have "[w‚á©0 ‚ä® ¬´desc œÜ¬ª‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® ¬´œÜ (desc œÜ)¬ª]"
103      by blast
104  } note 1 = this
105  moreover {
106    fix œÜ :: ‚Äπ'a ‚áí ùóà‚Ä∫
107    assume nex1: ‚Äπ‚àÑ! Œ∫ . [w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}]‚Ä∫
108    hence "(desc œÜ) = nondenoting œÜ" by (simp add: desc_def AOT_sem_denotes)
109    hence "[w ‚ä® ¬¨¬´desc œÜ¬ª‚Üì]" for w
110      by (simp add: AOT_sem_denotes nondenoting AOT_sem_not)
111  }
112  ultimately have desc_denotes_simp:
113    ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´desc œÜ¬ª‚Üì] = (‚àÉ! Œ∫ . [w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}])‚Ä∫ for œÜ w
114    by (simp add: AOT_sem_denotes desc_def nondenoting)
115  have ‚Äπ(‚àÄœÜ w. [w ‚ä® ¬´desc œÜ¬ª‚Üì] = (‚àÉ!Œ∫. [w‚á©0 ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚àß [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}])) ‚àß
116    (‚àÄœÜ w. [w ‚ä® ¬´desc œÜ¬ª‚Üì] ‚ü∂ [w‚á©0 ‚ä® ¬´œÜ (desc œÜ)¬ª]) ‚àß
117    (‚àÄœÜ w Œ∫. [w ‚ä® ¬´desc œÜ¬ª‚Üì] ‚ü∂ [w ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì] ‚ü∂ [w‚á©0 ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫}] ‚ü∂
118             [w ‚ä® ¬´desc œÜ¬ª = Œ∫])‚Ä∫
119    by (insert 1; auto simp: desc_denotes_simp AOT_sem_eq AOT_sem_denotes
120                             desc_def nondenoting)
121  thus ?thesis
122    by (safe intro!: exI[where x=desc]; presburger)
123qed

125text‚Äπ\linelabel{AOT_exe_lambda_spec}‚Ä∫
126specification(AOT_exe AOT_lambda)
127  ‚Äï ‚ÄπTruth conditions of exemplification formulas.‚Ä∫
128  AOT_sem_exe: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® [Œ†]Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n] = ([w ‚ä® Œ†‚Üì] ‚àß [w ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n‚Üì] ‚àß
129                                     [w ‚ä® ¬´Rep_rel Œ† Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n¬ª])‚Ä∫
130  ‚Äï ‚ÄπŒ∑-conversion for denoting terms; equivalent to AOT's axiom‚Ä∫
131  AOT_sem_lambda_eta: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® Œ†‚Üì] ‚üπ [w ‚ä® [ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n [Œ†]ŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n] = Œ†]‚Ä∫
132  ‚Äï ‚ÄπŒ≤-conversion; equivalent to AOT's axiom‚Ä∫
133  AOT_sem_lambda_beta: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® [ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n œÜ{ŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n}]‚Üì] ‚üπ [w ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n‚Üì] ‚üπ
134                        [w ‚ä® [ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n œÜ{ŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n}]Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n] = [w ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n}]‚Ä∫
135  ‚Äï ‚ÄπNecessary and sufficient conditions for relations to denote. Equivalent
136      to a theorem of AOT and used to derive the base cases of denoting relations
137      (cqt.2).‚Ä∫
138  AOT_sem_lambda_denotes: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® [ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n œÜ{ŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n}]‚Üì] =
139    (‚àÄ v Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n Œ∫‚á©1'Œ∫‚á©n' . [v ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n‚Üì] ‚àß [v ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1'...Œ∫‚á©n'‚Üì] ‚àß
140        (‚àÄ Œ† v . [v ‚ä® Œ†‚Üì] ‚ü∂ [v ‚ä® [Œ†]Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n] = [v ‚ä® [Œ†]Œ∫‚á©1'...Œ∫‚á©n']) ‚ü∂
141                 [v ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n}] = [v ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫‚á©1'...Œ∫‚á©n'}])‚Ä∫
142  ‚Äï ‚ÄπEquivalent to AOT's coexistence axiom.‚Ä∫
143  AOT_sem_lambda_coex: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® [ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n œÜ{ŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n}]‚Üì] ‚üπ
144    (‚àÄ w Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n . [w ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n‚Üì] ‚ü∂ [w ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n}] = [w ‚ä® œà{Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n}]) ‚üπ
145    [w ‚ä® [ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n œà{ŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n}]‚Üì]‚Ä∫
146  ‚Äï ‚ÄπOnly the unary case of the following should hold, but our specification
147      has to range over all types. We might move @{const AOT_exe} and
148      @{const AOT_lambda} to type classes in the future to solve this.‚Ä∫
149  AOT_sem_lambda_eq_prop_eq: ‚Äπ¬´[ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n œÜ]¬ª = ¬´[ŒªŒΩ‚á©1...ŒΩ‚á©n œà]¬ª ‚üπ œÜ = œà‚Ä∫
150  ‚Äï ‚ÄπThe following is solely required for validating n-ary relation identity
151      and has the danger of implying artifactual theorems. Possibly avoidable
152      by moving @{const AOT_exe} and @{const AOT_lambda} to type classes.‚Ä∫
153  AOT_sem_exe_denoting: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® Œ†‚Üì] ‚üπ AOT_exe Œ† Œ∫s = Rep_rel Œ† Œ∫s‚Ä∫
154  ‚Äï ‚ÄπThe following is required for validating the base cases of denoting
155      relations (cqt.2). A version of this meta-logical identity will
156      become derivable in future versions of AOT, so this will ultimately not
157      result in artifactual theorems.‚Ä∫
158  AOT_sem_exe_equiv: ‚ÄπAOT_model_term_equiv x y ‚üπ AOT_exe Œ† x = AOT_exe Œ† y‚Ä∫
159proof -
160  have ‚Äπ‚àÉ x :: <'a> . ¬¨AOT_model_denotes x‚Ä∫
161    by (rule exI[where x=‚ÄπAbs_rel (Œª x . Œµ‚á©ùóà w. True)‚Ä∫])
162       (meson AOT_model_denotes_rel.abs_eq AOT_model_nondenoting_ex
163              AOT_model_proposition_choice_simp)
164  define exe :: ‚Äπ<'a> ‚áí 'a ‚áí ùóà‚Ä∫ where
165    ‚Äπexe ‚â° Œª Œ† Œ∫s . if AOT_model_denotes Œ†
166                     then Rep_rel Œ† Œ∫s
167                     else (Œµ‚á©ùóà w . False)‚Ä∫
168  define lambda :: ‚Äπ('a‚áíùóà) ‚áí <'a>‚Ä∫ where
169    ‚Äπlambda ‚â° Œª œÜ . if AOT_model_denotes (Abs_rel œÜ)
170      then (Abs_rel œÜ)
171      else
172        if (‚àÄ Œ∫ Œ∫' w . (AOT_model_denotes Œ∫ ‚àß AOT_model_term_equiv Œ∫ Œ∫') ‚ü∂
173                       [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫¬ª] = [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫'¬ª])
174        then
175          Abs_rel (fix_irregular (Œª x . if AOT_model_denotes x
176                                        then œÜ (SOME y . AOT_model_term_equiv x y)
177                                        else  (Œµ‚á©ùóà w . False)))
178        else 
179          Abs_rel œÜ‚Ä∫
180  have fix_irregular_denoting_simp[simp]:
181    ‚Äπfix_irregular (Œªx. if AOT_model_denotes x then œÜ x else œà x) Œ∫ = œÜ Œ∫‚Ä∫
182    if ‚ÄπAOT_model_denotes Œ∫‚Ä∫
183    for Œ∫ :: 'a and œÜ œà
184    by (simp add: that fix_irregular_denoting)
185  have denoting_eps_cong[cong]:
186    ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ (Eps (AOT_model_term_equiv Œ∫))¬ª] = [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫¬ª]‚Ä∫
187    if ‚ÄπAOT_model_denotes Œ∫‚Ä∫
188    and ‚Äπ‚àÄ Œ∫ Œ∫'. AOT_model_denotes Œ∫ ‚àß AOT_model_term_equiv Œ∫ Œ∫' ‚ü∂
189                 (‚àÄw. [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫¬ª] = [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫'¬ª])‚Ä∫
190    for w :: w and Œ∫ :: 'a and œÜ :: ‚Äπ'a‚áíùóà‚Ä∫
191    using that AOT_model_term_equiv_eps(2) by blast
192  have exe_rep_rel: ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´exe Œ† Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n¬ª] = ([w ‚ä® Œ†‚Üì] ‚àß [w ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n‚Üì] ‚àß
193                                            [w ‚ä® ¬´Rep_rel Œ† Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n¬ª])‚Ä∫ for w Œ† Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n
194    by (metis AOT_model_denotes_rel.rep_eq exe_def AOT_sem_denotes
195              AOT_model_proposition_choice_simp)
196  moreover have ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´Œ†¬ª‚Üì] ‚üπ [w ‚ä® ¬´lambda (exe Œ†)¬ª = ¬´Œ†¬ª]‚Ä∫ for Œ† w
197    by (auto simp: Rep_rel_inverse lambda_def AOT_sem_denotes AOT_sem_eq
198                   AOT_model_denotes_rel_def Abs_rel_inverse exe_def)
199  moreover have lambda_denotes_beta:
200    ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´exe (lambda œÜ) Œ∫ ¬ª] = [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫¬ª]‚Ä∫
201    if ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´lambda œÜ¬ª‚Üì]‚Ä∫ and ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´Œ∫¬ª‚Üì]‚Ä∫
202    for œÜ Œ∫ w
203    using that unfolding exe_def AOT_sem_denotes
204    by (auto simp: lambda_def Abs_rel_inverse split: if_split_asm)
205  moreover have lambda_denotes_simp:
206    ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´lambda œÜ¬ª‚Üì] = (‚àÄ v Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n Œ∫‚á©1'Œ∫‚á©n' . [v ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n‚Üì] ‚àß [v ‚ä® Œ∫‚á©1'...Œ∫‚á©n'‚Üì] ‚àß
207        (‚àÄ Œ† v . [v ‚ä® Œ†‚Üì] ‚ü∂ [v ‚ä® ¬´exe Œ† Œ∫‚á©1Œ∫‚á©n¬ª] = [v ‚ä® ¬´exe Œ† Œ∫‚á©1'Œ∫‚á©n'¬ª]) ‚ü∂
208        [v ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫‚á©1...Œ∫‚á©n}] = [v ‚ä® œÜ{Œ∫‚á©1'...Œ∫‚á©n'}])‚Ä∫ for œÜ w
209  proof
210    assume ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´lambda œÜ¬ª‚Üì]‚Ä∫
211    hence ‚ÄπAOT_model_denotes (lambda œÜ)‚Ä∫
212      unfolding AOT_sem_denotes by simp
213    moreover have ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫¬ª] ‚üπ [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫'¬ª]‚Ä∫
214      and ‚Äπ[w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫'¬ª] ‚üπ [w ‚ä® ¬´œÜ Œ∫¬ª]‚Ä∫
215      if ‚ÄπAOT_model_denotes Œ∫‚Ä∫ and ‚ÄπAOT_model_term_equiv Œ∫ Œ∫'‚Ä∫
216      for w Œ∫ Œ∫'
217      by (metis (no_types, lifting) AOT_model_denotes_rel.abs_eq lambda_def

1695lemma AOT_sem_indistinguishable_ord_enc_ex:
1696  assumes Œ†_den: ‚Äπ[v ‚ä® Œ†‚Üì]‚Ä∫
1697  assumes Ax: ‚Äπ[v ‚ä® A!x]‚Ä∫
1698  assumes Ay: ‚Äπ[v ‚ä® A!y]‚Ä∫
1699  assumes indist: ‚Äπ[v ‚ä® ‚àÄF ‚ñ°([F]x ‚â° [F]y)]‚Ä∫
1700  shows ‚Äπ[v ‚ä® ‚àÉG(‚àÄz (O!z ‚Üí ‚ñ°([G]z ‚â° [Œ†]z)) & x[G])] =
1701         [v ‚ä® ‚àÉG(‚àÄz(O!z ‚Üí ‚ñ°([G]z ‚â° [Œ†]z)) & y[G])]‚Ä∫
1702proof -
1703  have Aux: ‚Äπ[v ‚ä® [Œªx ‚óá[E!]x]Œ∫] = ([v ‚ä® [Œªx ‚óá[E!]x]Œ∫] ‚àß [v ‚ä® Œ∫‚Üì])‚Ä∫ for v Œ∫
1704    using AOT_sem_exe by blast
1705  AOT_modally_strict {
1706    fix x y
1707    AOT_assume Œ†_den: ‚Äπ[Œ†]‚Üì‚Ä∫
1708    AOT_assume 2: ‚Äπ‚àÄF ‚ñ°([F]x ‚â° [F]y)‚Ä∫

1713    AOT_hence 1: ‚Äπ[Œªx ¬¨‚óá[E!]x]y‚Ä∫
1714      by (simp add: AOT_sem_abstract)
1715    {

1717      then AOT_obtain Œ†'
1718        where Œ†'_den: ‚ÄπŒ†'‚Üì‚Ä∫
1719          and Œ†'_indist: ‚Äπ‚àÄz (O!z ‚Üí ‚ñ°([Œ†']z ‚â° [Œ†]z))‚Ä∫
1720          and x_enc_Œ†': ‚Äπx[Œ†']‚Ä∫
1721        by (meson AOT_sem_conj AOT_sem_exists)
1722      {
1723        fix Œ∫‚á©0

1726          using Œ†'_indist
1727          by (auto simp: AOT_sem_exe AOT_sem_imp AOT_sem_exists AOT_sem_conj
1728                         AOT_sem_ordinary AOT_sem_forall)
1729      } note 3 = this
1730      AOT_have ‚Äπ‚àÄz ([Œªx ‚óá[E!]x]z ‚Üí ‚ñ°([Œ†']z ‚â° [Œ†]z))‚Ä∫
1731        using Œ†'_indist by (simp add: AOT_sem_ordinary)
1732      AOT_obtain Œ†'' where
1733          Œ†''_den: ‚ÄπŒ†''‚Üì‚Ä∫ and
1734          Œ†''_indist: ‚Äπ[Œªx ‚óá[E!]x]Œ∫‚á©0 ‚Üí ‚ñ°([Œ†'']Œ∫‚á©0 ‚â° [Œ†]Œ∫‚á©0)‚Ä∫ and
1735          y_enc_Œ†'': ‚Äπy[Œ†'']‚Ä∫ for Œ∫‚á©0
1736        using AOT_sem_enc_indistinguishable_ex[OF AOT_ExtendedModel,
1737                OF 0, OF 1, rotated, OF Œ†_den,
1738                OF exI[where x=Œ†'], OF conjI, OF Œ†'_den, OF conjI,
1739                OF x_enc_Œ†', OF allI, OF impI,
1740                OF 3[simplified AOT_sem_box AOT_sem_equiv], simplified, OF

1742                  THEN spec, THEN mp, THEN spec], simplified]
1743        unfolding AOT_sem_imp AOT_sem_box AOT_sem_equiv by blast
1744      {

1746            and ‚Äπ‚àÄx ([Œªx ‚óá[E!]x]x ‚Üí ‚ñ°([Œ†'']x ‚â° [Œ†]x))‚Ä∫

1749          apply (simp add: AOT_sem_forall Œ†''_indist)

1751      } note 2 = this

1759  AOT_modally_strict {
